rcli
------------------------------------------
rcli is a powerful C++ library that simplifies the creation of CLI
applications. It provides convenient user input functions and efficiently
manages command-line options and subcommands.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.1-1
  libgcc1-11.4.0-1
  librcli-devel-1.5.2-1bl1
  librcli1-1.5.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.1.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.42-1
  cmake-3.25.3-1
  cygport-0.36.8-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.4.0-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/RickaPrincy/rcli

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/RickaPrincy/rcli/archive/refs/tags/v1.5.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rcli-1.5.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rcli-1.5.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rcli-1.5.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rcli-1.5.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librcli1-1.5.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librcli-devel-1.5.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rcli)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rcli.README
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/README.md

(librcli1)
  /usr/bin/cygrcli-1.dll

(librcli-devel)
  /usr/include/TColor/TColor.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/app.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/color_config.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/command.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/input_config.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/inputs.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/option.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/rcli.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/types.hpp
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliTargets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/librcli.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/rcli.pc

